  "texts": [
    "For the main comparative assessment results, we consider the full set of possible comparisons, where all pairs of candidates in both permutations are compared by the framework.",
    "Comparisons are made using the prompt-based classifier (as described in §3.3) using the prompt templates shown in Fig. 2, where the system outputs a probability for Response A and Response B.",
    "The winner of the comparison is the response with the highest probability, where candidates are then ranked in order of the win-ratio (as described in §3.4).",
    "For Llama2, comparative prompts are appended with 'Answer:' while scoring prompts end with 'Score:'.",
    "The spearman correlation between predicted scores and human judgements is used as the performance metric."
  ],
